description.en:
On the basis of this course the students will learn the:
- translating of Old-Babylonian poetic texts;
- analyzing their grammar, phonology, morphology and syntax;
- dealing with some aspects of a textual critical analysis of appropriate poetic texts.

description.et:
Üliõpilased õpivad:
- tõlkima Vana-Babüloonia luuletekste;
- analüüsima nende grammatikat, fonoloogiat, morfoloogiat ja süntaksit;
- tegelema luuletekstide tekstikriitilise analüüsi mõne aspektiga.

objectives.en:
The aim of this course is to:
- get an overview of the grammatical and syntactical structure, phonology and morphology of the Babylonian language of the Old Babylonian period (1st half of the 2nd Millennium B.C.); 
- study the basics of translating appropriate poetic texts like the prologue of the Codex Hammurapi.
